The paper discusses the problem of causal discovery from data, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus of the paper is on constraint-based approaches, which are widely used in causal discovery due to their fast running speed and easy generalization to the problem of causal insufficiency. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
